Description: Product Maintenance - Netwrix Endpoint Protector 5.9.4.1 Focuses on Security, Manageability, and User Experience. (HWA-EPP4-U0066)
Netwrix Endpoint Protector 5.9.4.1 introduces significant updates designed to enhance security, streamline management, and improve user experience. Benefit from improved detection of sensitive information in cloud prints, patch critical vulnerabilities, and meet stricter password management requirements. Manage your environment with ease using simplified group management, accurate device inventory, and clearer user distinction. Enjoy a more intuitive interface that empowers you to work efficiently.
Remarks: Applies to version: 5.9.4.0
Some problems occurred during installation. Please Contact Support. (ERROR: 2 - Number of maximum retries for this update reached, skipping this update...)

Next Steps:

  1. Run Erroneous patch procedure
  2. then upgrade to 5941.
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Alin Anca, Jens Balk
Steps to Reproduce Updated: Upgrade to the latest server version
What We've Learned Updated: The patch was finishing in the Mysql table on NULL, I deleted that entry and after that it went through.
Next Steps Updated: Connect to the customer and remove that patch
